a. Any member of our group, which means our subsidiaries, our ultimate holding company, and its subsidiaries;
b. Selected third parties including (this list is not exhaustive):
3.2 analytics and search engine providers that assist us in the improvement and optimization of the EmCan Mobile App or Website.
3.3 If we are under a duty to disclose or share your personal data to comply with any legal or audit obligation, or to enforce or apply the terms governing the EmCan Mobile App or Website and other agreements, or to protect our rights, property, or safety, our customers, or others or in relation to information security breach investigation and/or notification. This includes exchanging information with other companies and organizations for the purposes of fraud protection or risk control or for any legal or regulatory purpose.
4. Where we store your personal data
4.1 The data that we collect from you may usually be stored in the United Kingdom, but we may transfer, store or process it in the UAE or other jurisdictions. By submitting your personal data, you agree to this transfer, storing, or processing either within or outside of the UAE. We will take all steps reasonably practicable to ensure that your data is treated securely and in accordance with this privacy policy. If you do not consent to your data being stored outside of the UAE, you can exercise your right to prevent such storage by notifying us in writing as soon as you start using EmCaan Mobile App or Website.
4.2 We use information held about you in accordance with the relevant terms governing the EmCan Mobile App or Website and (this list is not exhaustive):
4.3 Unfortunately, the transmission of information via the internet is not completely secure. Although we will do our best to protect your personal data, we cannot guarantee the security of your data transmitted to any digital platform used for the EmCan Mobile App or Website; any transmission is at your own risk. Once we have received your information, we will use strict procedures and security features to try to prevent unauthorized access.
5. Use of Face ID for iOS Device Login:
EmCan offers the option to log in using Face ID, a facial recognition technology provided by Apple Inc. This feature is available on compatible iOS devices equipped with Face ID functionality.
5.1 How Face ID Works:
Face ID scans and analyzes your facial features to securely authenticate your identity for logging into EmCan. Your facial data is processed locally on your device and is not transmitted to our servers.
5.2 Data Collected and Stored:
When you choose to use Face ID for login, we do not collect or store any facial recognition data. Apple's Face ID technology manages and secures your facial data within the device's hardware and software.
5.3 Purpose of Face ID Usage:
We use Face ID solely for the purpose of enhancing the security and convenience of your login experience. It provides a secure and efficient method of authentication, reducing the need for entering passwords.
